verbose_text: Most importantly, we provided the in vivo evidence showing that the NPs-alphaIL6R Ab-CD44 treatment impeded the metastasis of breast cancer in both the 4T1-xenograft mouse model and MMTV-PyMT model through down-regulating the production of cytokines or enzymes such as VEGFA and MMP-9 as well as inhibiting the angiogenesis.
evidence: NPs-alphaIL6R Ab-CD44 treatment impeded the metastasis
